jobs.description:
The future of transportation is already here.

Alstom, with recorded sales of 7.3 billion in the 2016/17 fiscal year, is the world leader in integrated transport systems and continues to push the boundaries of innovation &amp; digital solutions for transportation systems and e-mobility. We are at the forefront of providing sustainable modes of transport with the largest range of rail solutions in the market. Headquartered in France, we are present in over 60 countries and today employ 32,800 people worldwide.

For more information, please visit: http://www.alstom.com/

We are looking for a

PROJECT MATERIAL MANAGER

PURPOSE OF THE JOB
• Coordinate, consolidate and secure QCD commitments within the Material Scope (Metier) in Project Execution. Transversally through the different work packages. Having end to end accountability regardless of if it is Make or Buy.
• Manage industrial scope assigned by the DIS project ensuring that the products are delivered to the project stakeholders... according to project QCD commitments.
• Work as interface in the core Team meeting representing both Procurement function and Operations/Supply Chain function.

POSITION IN THE ORGANIZATION

Represent the Industrial Operations organization within the project core team

NETWORK &amp; LINKS
• Project core team members;
• Support functions: Project Industrial Management, Industrialization, Manufacturing, Supply Chain, Planning, Logistics, Sourcing.

MISSION &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES

For Project Execution, the Project Material Manager should:
• Get QCD commitment as built at tender phase in the respective LU- Leading Unit and Pus- Participating Unit, secure the commitments are well understood by the Project, Industrial, Supply Chain and Procurement team;
• Ensure that necessary inputs data allowing respect of QCD commitment are consistently and timely made available by other project contributors;
• Define industrial scheme and related make or buy strategy;
• Check completeness and on time availability of the detailed design (under PrEM/ Engineer responsibility);
• Coordinate and supervises the Industrial Operations that are in charge of the following tasks: supervision of material procurement, products manufacturing and testing, logistic &amp; shipment;
• Supervise cash flow curve related to material orders and minimize the time the material remains in the warehouse. Support project closure to clean and close the Hard Inventory;
• Have a general vision of the Project’s / suppliers' progress, stakes, and difficulties. Define and agree with Procurement the capture or mitigation plans to be followed by Procurement;
• Manage the Material EAC/TAC (Estimation at Completion/ Total at Completion), Co-validating ASIP savings, Co-Validates with Sub-System Manager each gap vs CPR0 (deviation sheet &amp; bridge approval process) with escalation to Project and procurement team in case of need for arbitration.

REQUIREMENTS:
• Degree in Management Engineering or equivalent;
• Experience of at least 5 years in project or industrial management roles;
• Consolidated knowledge and experience in Industrial Operation field;
• Professional knowledge of English;
• Basic knowledge on SAP (or others ERP system);
• Good knowledge on office automation suit (Excel, Outlook)
• Attitude to teamworking and to collaborate with people of various departments both internal (Project Management, Supply Chain, Industrialization, Manufacturing, Sales, Product Development, Sourcing) and external (suppliers).

Alstom is committed to create a diverse &amp; international working environment, that reflects the future of our industry, our clients and end-users. As an employee, you will have a unique opportunity to continue to build your career and directly contribute to the expanding growth of the global transport industry

Job Type:​Experienced​

Il nostro cliente, realtà leader nella fornitura di soluzioni industriali, ci ha incaricati di selezionare la seguente figura professionale:

Direttore Commerciale Italia

La risorsa, a diretto riporto della Direzione, dovrà garantire il raggiungimento degli obiettivi di vendita qualitativi e quantitativi, sviluppando strategie commerciali, supportando la forza vendita diretta ed indiretta nella gestione di problematiche e ottimizzando la marginalità delle vendite.

La figura avrà le seguenti responsabilità:
• Coordinamento e gestione delle risorse dirette e indirette e sviluppo della rete vendita italiana;
• Sviluppo delle strategie di vendita e delle campagne promozionali definendo condizioni di pricing ed incentivi;
• Elaborazione di budgets di vendita e target con il monitoraggio di risultati di vendita;
• Analizzare eventuali problematiche ed individuare aree di miglioramento;
• Supervisionare i contratti formalizzati dalla rete vendita, per verificare il rispetto delle... condizioni commerciali pattuite;
• Gestione della priorità delle preventivazioni e dei progetti esecutivi e definizione di accordi quadro con i clienti;
• Formulazione dei contratti che regolano le relazioni tra l’azienda e gli agenti o i segnalatori;
• Gestione diretta di clienti direzionali, per gli aspetti negoziali, organizzativi e di feedback sull’andamento dei lavori in essere;
• Partecipazione ai processi organizzativi dei flussi di dati legati alle vendite (report vendite, archivio dati);
• Collaborazione con la direzione per implementare processi organizzativi (assicurazioni, Zero service, sviluppo configuratori);

Competenze:
• Formazione accademica ad indirizzo economico o equipollenti;
• Esperienza di almeno 5 anni nella gestione rete di vendita;
• Spiccate doti analitiche e di problem solving
• Buon utilizzo dei principali sistemi informatici.

Sede di lavoro: Provincia di Vicenza

Wyser è la società internazionale di Gi Group che si occupa di ricerca e selezione di middle e senior management specializzato. Facciamo parte di Gi Group, una delle principali realtà a livello internazionale nei servizi dedicati allo sviluppo del mercato del lavoro.

#LI-BF1

Description

For our Business Unit High Voltage based in Lodi we are looking for a Project manager who will be responsible for leading the execution of multiple projects and ensuring that all related activities are executed in accordance with company procedures, contract specifications, quality standards, health, safety &amp; environment requirements, cost/profitability targets and scheduling targets.

Your responsibilities:

1. Define, jointly with the Project Controls department, all project plan documents, including scope and financial plans, schedule and risk management plans;

2. Ensure that the project follows execution best practices and company policies. Effectively monitor and control project progress and efficient resource utilization. Monitor and control project financials, overseeing project invoicing status, cost, expenses and cash flow. Identify, qualify, quantify and manage risk, and ensure that all opportunities are identified and pursued. Capture, analyze and share... lessons learned throughout the project. Ensure that the project is formally closed out, as contractually agreed. Drive the formal acceptance of the project, contract close-out and its acknowledgement by the customer;

3. Ensure that the project consistently applies contract and claims management, in accordance with company policies and contractual agreements. Coordinate with Supply Chain Management, and successfully procure required services, materials and equipment for the project from external and internal suppliers. Support Supply Chain Management in negotiations, claims and project changes;

4. Act as key contact for the customer and an escalation point for project issues. Build and maintain strong relationships with internal and external stakeholders and effectively communicate with all stakeholders;

5. Ensure the project follows and complies with company health, safety, and environmental policies;

6. Live core values of safety and integrity, which means taking responsibility for your own actions while caring for your colleagues, and the business.

Your background:
• Engineering degree;
• Previous experience in Project management of at least 2 years;
• Excellent knowledge of English and Italian language;
• Good problem solving and communication skills;
• Certification PMI/PMP is a plus;
• SAP knowledge is a plus
